  PLAIN VERDICT: NO candidate quotient definition (rel_sub, rel_col, surv, surv2,
  nor raw chi or D) is constant in M0 -- neither globally nor at fixed A.
  The Lean-certificate demand 'relIndex = -5 CONSTANT for all M0 >= 5' is REFUTED
  for every natural quotient tested here. chi(cone3) = -5 at (5,4) is a genuine
  but ISOLATED calibration point of one small cone, not a scale-stable invariant.

  The ONE exact stability that DOES hold: on cones (fixed apex c) the sector-relative
  candidates ['rel_sub', 'rel_col', 'surv', 'surv2'] are exactly invariant under the absorber horizon M0
  (verified M0 = 4 vs 89 on every scanned apex, A = 5, 7, 11). The quotient by the
  killed sector cancels the M0-dependence EXACTLY -- but the resulting index is a
  function of the apex, not a constant.

  Actual scale law (Phase-4 parametrization): the survivor subcomplex is a complete
  transitive tournament, E_SS = C(V_S,2) exactly, hence
      surv2 = V_S (3 - V_S) / 2        (exact, all regions)
      rel_sub = surv - E_KS            (exact, all regions)
  and V_S = #clean centers <= top(region) grows linearly in the region height
  (density prod_{5<=q<=A}(q-2)/q), so every candidate is QUADRATIC in the height,
  not constant. See fits above.

